Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Mince a few @dill pickle{1%sliced} until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings).

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, ½ TBSP @Cajun spice blend{2%tablespoon} (you'll use more in the next step), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Secret Sauce ==

While potatoes roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @hot sauce{1%teaspoon}, minced pickle, and @sugar{¼%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4 servings).

> TIP: If you like things less spicy, add hot sauce to taste.

== Sour Cream Dip ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon} with 4 TBSP water (8 TBSP for 4); season with salt and pepper.

== Breading ==

In a #shallow dish{}, combine @flour{½%cup}, @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, 1 TBSP Cajun spice blend (2 TBSP for 4), 1 tsp salt (2 tsp for 4), and pepper. (You'll use the rest of the Cajun Spice Blend in the next step.)

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Place between two large pieces of #plastic wrap{}; pound with a #mallet{} or #heavy-bottomed pan{} until about 1⁄3 inch thick. Season all over with salt, pepper, and remaining Cajun Spice Blend.

Working one piece at a time, coat chicken in flour mixture, then dip into sour cream mixture until fully coated on both sides; press again into flour mixture. Shake off excess flour and set aside on a #plate{}.

Heat a 1⁄3-inch layer of oil in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of flour mixture sizzles immediately when added to the pan, add coated chicken. Cook until golden brown and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Fry in batches if necessary; lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate. Season with salt.

== Assembly ==

While chicken cooks, halve and toast @brioche buns{2}.

Spread cut sides of buns with @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings).

Spread cut sides of buns with secret sauce. Fill buns with chicken and as much sliced pickle as you like.

Divide sandwiches between plates and serve with potato wedges on the side.

> TIP: If you have some on hand, serve with ketchup for dipping.